Your function is almost correct, except that you did not use `s` as parameter for the function application with `s`:

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;func:: (String -&amp;gt; String) -&amp;gt; String -&amp;gt; String
func f s = reverse s ++ f &lt;b&gt;s&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

You furthermore use the function the wrong way, since the first parameter is not a string, but a function that maps a string on a string. We can for example use [**`id :: a -&gt; a`**](https://hackage.haskell.org/package/base-4.12.0.0/docs/Prelude.html#v:id) to return `s`, or [**`reverse :: [a] -&gt; [a]`**](https://hackage.haskell.org/package/base-4.12.0.0/docs/Prelude.html#v:reverse) to reverse the string:

    Prelude&gt; func id &quot;haskell&quot;
    &quot;lleksahhaskell&quot;
    Prelude&gt; func reverse &quot;haskell&quot;
    &quot;lleksahlleksah&quot;

