Here is an example using **Fractional**, it will preserve the correct precision of the input numbers, and does only one traversal of the data. However, do note that this only works for types that have a _&quot;precise&quot;_ division, like `Float`, `Double` &amp; `BigDecimal`. But does not work for numeric types like `Int` or `Long`.

    def mean[T](data: Iterable[T])(implicit N: Fractional[T]): T = {
      import N._
    
      val remaining = data.iterator
    
      @annotation.tailrec
      def loop(sum: T, count: Int): T =
        if (remaining.hasNext)
          loop(sum + remaining.next(), count + 1)
        else if (count == 0)
          zero
        else
          sum / fromInt(count)
    
      loop(zero, 0)
    }

